Yeah, I think a lot of pretenders do try to find ways to promote themselves
into more credibility.  In fact, I wonder about that project you are going
to be doing with Mr Moon.  It&#39;s my guess he is the one who suggested it
(maybe even dropped some profitability hints?).  Realize, his method of
performing medium with the box, and charging the vulnerable large amounts of
money, is under attack from many quarters, and he has begun to go on the
defensive.  One thing that is hard for him to defend, is how he can be so
expert with the box when he had nothing to do with its construction.

Now consider, if he can get the box&#39;s maker to participate in a project
together, even just once, he can add to his list of credentials things such
as &quot;Worked together with the original box&#39;s designer, Frank Sumption, on new
designs.&quot; Or even &quot;Co-creater of the new Box&quot;, whatever it is.

You will be giving him that very credibility, that those &quot;do my shows&quot; are
looking for.  Maybe even getting him new customers.  Just by associating
with him on one project.

My advice is, be careful that you aren&#39;t just being used for your
credentials Frank.



